name: FLYING CANADA'S SHORTEST 737 FLIGHT? Air North 737-500 Victoria to Vancouver
description:
Victoria to Vancouver is one of Canada's shortest, yet busiest commercial air routes.

One oddity on this route is Air North's Boeing 737, which flies it as part of a triangle routing, flying Whitehorse-Victoria-Vancouver-Whitehorse.

With just 63 kilometres between airports, is this Canada's shortest commercial 737 flight?

Thanks to Brandon Siska for the thumbnail photo!
